    "what_description": "Witheringia dentata is a flowering plant species in the family Solanaceae. It is an evergreen shrub with entire or dentate leaves that are 6-18 cm long and have 5-7 pairs of secondary veins. The leaves are glabrous or pubescent on the lower surface, and the plant produces white to purple flowers in axillary cymes, each with 5-6 petals and a 5-6 mm long corolla tube. The fruit is a globose berry, 6-8 mm in diameter, with a glabrous or pubescent surface and a single seed per locule. Witheringia dentata is native to the Andes of South America, specifically in Ecuador and Peru.",
